{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852182133,"sessionID":"ses_286f6aed7ffekYy405f9z7HzpW","part":{"id":"prt_d7909cf4d001ZzMBL5GC6SkRZ9","messageID":"msg_d7909b2a9001BzVssdQ4e7Q6pY","sessionID":"ses_286f6aed7ffekYy405f9z7HzpW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-1343ff9d890b413b9b4037897f06673e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement session management for the AgentCube Router component. This provides the core session resolution and sandbox creation logic that enables session-aware routing. The session management component:\n6: \n7: 1. **Session Resolution**: Reads `x-agentcube-session-id` header, looks up existing `SandboxInfo` from the Store when present\n8: 2. **Sandbox Creation**: When session ID is empty, creates new sandboxes via Workload Manager HTTP API\n9: 3. **Response Validation**: Parses `CreateSandboxResponse` from Workload Manager and builds in-memory `SandboxInfo` with session metadata\n10: 4. **Store Integration**: Persists sandbox info to Store after successful creation for subsequent session lookups\n11: 5. **Error Handling**: Maps Workload Manager errors to Router-specific error types (NotFound, Timeout, etc.)\n12: 6. **Service Account Auth**: Attaches Kubernetes service account token for in-cluster Workload Manager authentication\n13: \n14: ## Scope\n15: \n16: ### In Scope\n17: \n18: | Deliverable | Description |\n19: |-------------|-------------|\n20: | `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager interface implementation with GetSandboxBySession, createSandbox logic |\n21: | `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | Unit tests for session resolution, sandbox creation, error handling, HTTP client behavior |\n22: | `pkg/router/doc.go` | SessionManager interface definition, Store interface, Logger interface |\n23: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | SessionNotFoundError, WorkloadManagerError types with APIStatus implementation |\n24: | Environment configuration | WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL required, optional service account token reading |\n25: | HTTP client setup | Timeout 2m, MaxIdleConnsPerHost 100, HTTP2 transport configuration |\n26: \n27: ### Key Components\n28: \n29: ```\n30: pkg/router/\n31: ├── SessionManager (doc.go)\n32: │   ├── Interface: GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)\n33: │   ├── Dependencies: Store (for sandbox lookup/storage), Workload Manager HTTP client\n34: │   └── Lifecycle: NewSessionManager validates WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, builds HTTP client\n35: │\n36: ├── sessionManager struct (session_manager.go)\n37: │   ├── storeClient: Store interface implementation\n38: │   ├── workloadMgrAddr: Workload Manager service URL\n39: │   ├── httpClient: *http.Client with HTTP2, 2m timeout, 100 idle conns\n40: │   └── GetSandboxBySession: sessionID empty → createSandbox, else → store lookup\n41: │\n42: ├── createSandbox (session_manager.go)\n43: │   ├── Validate CreateSandboxRequest (kind, namespace, name)\n44: │   ├── Route by kind: AgentRuntime → /v1/agent-runtime, CodeInterpreter → /v1/code-interpreter\n45: │   ├── POST JSON request to Workload Manager\n46: │   ├── Attach Authorization header with SA token if available\n47: │   ├── Parse CreateSandboxResponse (SessionID, SandboxID, SandboxName, EntryPoints)\n48: │   ├── Build SandboxInfo with default expiresAt (30m), status \"Running\"\n49: │   └── Store to Store via StoreSandbox\n50: │\n51: └── Errors (errors.go)\n52:     ├── SessionNotFoundError: sessionID not found in store → 404\n53:     ├── WorkloadManagerError: HTTP error from WM → StatusCode + Msg\n54:     └── readServiceAccountToken: /var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\n55: ```\n56: \n57: ### Out of Scope\n58: \n59: - Reverse proxy implementation (covered by AR-009)\n60: - JWT token generation (covered by AR-009)\n61: - Concurrency limiting middleware (covered by AR-009)\n62: - Health endpoint handlers (covered by AR-009)\n63: - Store implementation details (covered by session-store spec)\n64: - Workload Manager implementation (covered by AR-006, AR-007)\n65: - Distributed session cache (Redis-based)\n66: - Session eviction/cleanup (covered by AR-008 GC)\n67: \n68: ## Impact Analysis\n69: \n70: ### Upstream Dependencies\n71: \n72: | Dependency | Impact |\n73: |------------|--------|\n74: | `pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response, kind constants (AgentRuntimeKind, CodeInterpreterKind) |\n75: | `pkg/router/doc.go` | Store interface (GetSandboxBySessionID, StoreSandbox), Logger interface |\n76: | `os.Getenv` | WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL required at construction |\n77: | `os.ReadFile` | Service account token from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n78: | `golang.org/x/net/http2` | HTTP2 transport configuration for Workload Manager client |\n79: | Workload Manager service | POST `/v1/agent-runtime`, `/v1/code-interpreter` endpoints |\n80: \n81: ### Downstream Consumers\n82: \n83: | Consumer | Usage |\n84: |----------|-------|\n85: | `Server.handleInvoke` | Calls GetSandboxBySession to resolve sandbox for proxy routing |\n86: | `Server.handleHealthReady` | Checks sessionManager nil for readiness probe |\n87: | Store implementations | Receives StoreSandbox calls after creation |\n88: | Workload Manager | Receives sandbox creation requests |\n89: | Reverse proxy | Uses SandboxInfo.EntryPoints for target URL selection |\n90: \n91: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n92: \n93: - **Session Header Name**: `x-agentcube-session-id` header is client contract; changing requires all clients to update\n94: - **Workload Manager URL**: Environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` must be set; startup fails if missing\n95: - **Kind Routing**: `/v1/agent-runtime` and `/v1/code-interpreter` paths are fixed contracts with Workload Manager\n96: - **Response Schema**: `CreateSandboxResponse` fields (sessionId, sandboxId, sandboxName, entryPoints) must be provided\n97: - **Default Expiry**: 30-minute default `ExpiresAt` affects sandbox lifecycle\n98: \n99: ## Alternatives Considered\n100: \n101: ### Alternative 1: Direct Kubernetes API Lookup\n102: \n103: **Approach**: Session manager directly queries Kubernetes API for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CRs instead of delegating to Workload Manager.\n104: \n105: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n106: |--------|------------|\n107: | Pros | No intermediate service; direct CR access; simpler architecture |\n108: | Cons | Router requires K8s client permissions; no sandbox pod endpoint resolution; no entry point mapping |\n109: \n110: **Decision**: Rejected. Workload Manager handles CR creation AND pod endpoint resolution (EntryPoints). Router needs pod addresses for proxying, not just CR status.\n111: \n112: ### Alternative 2: Session Cache in Router Memory\n113: \n114: **Approach**: Cache sandbox info in router process memory without Store dependency.\n115: \n116: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n117: |--------|------------|\n118: | Pros | Zero latency for lookups; no external store dependency |\n119: | Cons | Lost on router restart; no persistence; cannot share across router instances |\n120: \n121: **Decision**: Rejected. Store provides persistence across router restarts and enables idle timeout detection by GC component. Memory-only cache breaks session continuity.\n122: \n123: ### Alternative 3: Session ID Embedded in URL Path\n124: \n125: **Approach**: Include session ID in URL path like `/v1/sessions/:sessionId/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path`.\n126: \n127: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n128: |--------|------------|\n129: | Pros | Session visible in URL; no header dependency |\n130: | Cons | Breaks logical resource routing (namespace/name pattern); clients must track session IDs; URL pollution |\n131: \n132: **Decision**: Rejected. Header-based session ID (`x-agentcube-session-id`) allows clients to use logical names (namespace/name) while Router handles session state internally. This matches OpenAI-style API design.\n133: \n134: ### Alternative 4: No Session Creation on Router\n135: \n136: **Approach**: Router never creates sandboxes; clients must call Workload Manager directly for session creation.\n137: \n138: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n139: |--------|------------|\n140: | Pros | Router simpler; no Workload Manager client code |\n141: | Cons | Clients manage session lifecycle; two-step flow (create then invoke); no session abstraction benefit |\n142: \n143: **Decision**: Rejected. Session creation on first invocation (empty session ID) is core AgentCube design—clients use single invoke endpoint, Router handles creation transparently.\n144: \n145: ### Alternative 5: gRPC for Workload Manager Communication\n146: \n147: **Approach**: Use gRPC instead of HTTP for Workload Manager sandbox creation.\n148: \n149: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n150: |--------|------------|\n151: | Pros | Better performance; streaming support; typed contracts |\n152: | Cons | Requires gRPC service on Workload Manager; incompatible with HTTP-only deployment; adds protobuf dependency |\n153: \n154: **Decision**: Rejected. HTTP/JSON API aligns with Kubernetes ecosystem and REST API conventions. Both Router and Workload Manager already use HTTP stack (Gin, net/http).\n155: \n156: ## Risks\n157: \n158: | Risk | Mitigation |\n159: |------|------------|\n160: | Workload Manager unavailable | Startup fails with explicit error if WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL missing; HTTP client timeout 2m |\n161: | Workload Manager returns non-OK | WorkloadManagerError captures status code + body for debugging |\n162: | Empty SessionID in response | Validation returns error \"empty sessionId in response\" |\n163: | Store lookup fails | SessionNotFoundError with sessionID in error message |\n164: | Service account token unavailable | Optional; gracefully skipped if file doesn't exist |\n165: | Sandbox creation race (duplicate session) | Workload Manager handles deduplication; StoreSandbox may overwrite |\n166: | HTTP2 connection issues | ConfigureTransport with ReadIdleTimeout, PingTimeout for connection health |\n167: | Request body unmarshal failure | Error wrapped with context \"failed to parse response\" |\n168: \n169: ## Implementation Notes\n170: \n171: 1. **Environment Variables**: `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` (required), reads from `os.Getenv`\n172: 2. **HTTP Client**: Timeout 2 minutes, MaxIdleConnsPerHost 100, HTTP2 via `http2.ConfigureTransport`\n173: 3. **Service Account Token**: Path `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`, trimmed before use\n174: 4. **Default Namespace**: `IdentityNamespace = \"default\"` or from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env\n175: 5. **Request Validation**: `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` checks kind, namespace, name\n176: 6. **Endpoint Routing**: AgentRuntimeKind → `/v1/agent-runtime`, CodeInterpreterKind → `/v1/code-interpreter`\n177: 7. **Default Expiry**: `ExpiresAt = time.Now().Add(30 * time.Minute)` for new sandboxes\n178: 8. **Store Integration**: `StoreSandbox` called after successful creation; store handles persistence\n179: 9. **Error Types**: `SessionNotFoundError`, `WorkloadManagerError` implement `APIStatus` interface\n180: \n181: ## References\n182: \n183: - `session-routing/spec.md` - Full requirement specification\n184: - `pkg/router/session_manager.go` - Implementation\n185: - `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` - Test coverage\n186: - `pkg/router/doc.go` - Interface definitions\n187: - `pkg/router/errors.go` - Error types\n188: - `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` - SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response\n189: - `deployment/client-go.md` - Kubernetes client reference\n190: - `changes/AR-009/proposal.md` - Related Router HTTP reverse proxy proposal\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement session management for the AgentCube Router component. This provides the core session resolution and sandbox creation logic that enables session-aware routing. The session management component:\n\n1. **Session Resolution**: Reads `x-agentcube-session-id` header, looks up existing `SandboxInfo` from the Store when present\n2. **Sandbox Creation**: When session ID is empty, creates new sandboxes via Workload Manager HTTP API\n3. **Response Validation**: Parses `CreateSandboxResponse` from Workload Manager and builds in-memory `SandboxInfo` with session metadata\n4. **Store Integration**: Persists sandbox info to Store after successful creation for subsequent session lookups\n5. **Error Handling**: Maps Workload Manager errors to Router-specific error types (NotFound, Timeout, etc.)\n6. **Service Account Auth**: Attaches Kubernetes service account token for in-cluster Workload Manager authentication\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager interface implementation with GetSandboxBySession, createSandbox logic |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775852182108,"end":1775852182131}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852182135,"sessionID":"ses_286f6aed7ffekYy405f9z7HzpW","part":{"id":"prt_d7909d2c30014NHPV1OLSYgy9R","messageID":"msg_d7909b2a9001BzVssdQ4e7Q6pY","sessionID":"ses_286f6aed7ffekYy405f9z7HzpW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a4c952b53eb446cfac1ee6a5b1876cd6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/server.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/server.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package router\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"fmt\"\n6: \t\"net/http\"\n7: \t\"net/http/httputil\"\n8: \t\"time\"\n9: \n10: \t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n11: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n12: \tapierrors \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n13: )\n14: \n15: type Server struct {\n16: \tconfig         *Config\n17: \tengine         *gin.Engine\n18: \thttpServer     *http.Server\n19: \tsessionManager SessionManager\n20: \tstoreClient    Store\n21: \thttpTransport  *http.Transport\n22: \tjwtManager     *JWTManager\n23: \tlogger         Logger\n24: }\n25: \n26: func NewServer(config *Config, sessionManager SessionManager, storeClient Store, jwtManager *JWTManager, logger Logger) *Server {\n27: \tif config == nil {\n28: \t\tconfig = DefaultConfig()\n29: \t}\n30: \n31: \tif config.MaxConcurrentRequests <= 0 {\n32: \t\tconfig.MaxConcurrentRequests = 1000\n33: \t}\n34: \n35: \tif !config.Debug {\n36: \t\tgin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)\n37: \t} else {\n38: \t\tgin.SetMode(gin.DebugMode)\n39: \t}\n40: \n41: \tengine := gin.New()\n42: \n43: \thttpTransport := &http.Transport{\n44: \t\tMaxIdleConnsPerHost: 100,\n45: \t\tDisableCompression:  false,\n46: \t}\n47: \n48: \thttpServer := &http.Server{\n49: \t\tAddr:        config.Port,\n50: \t\tHandler:     engine,\n51: \t\tReadTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n52: \t\tIdleTimeout: 90 * time.Second,\n53: \t}\n54: \n55: \ts := &Server{\n56: \t\tconfig:         config,\n57: \t\tengine:         engine,\n58: \t\thttpServer:     httpServer,\n59: \t\tsessionManager: sessionManager,\n60: \t\tstoreClient:    storeClient,\n61: \t\thttpTransport:  httpTransport,\n62: \t\tjwtManager:     jwtManager,\n63: \t\tlogger:         logger,\n64: \t}\n65: \n66: \ts.registerRoutes()\n67: \n68: \treturn s\n69: }\n70: \n71: func (s *Server) registerRoutes() {\n72: \ts.engine.GET(\"/health/live\", s.handleHealthLive)\n73: \ts.engine.GET(\"/health/ready\", s.handleHealthReady)\n74: \n75: \tv1 := s.engine.Group(\"/v1/namespaces/:namespace\")\n76: \tv1.Use(concurrencyLimitMiddleware(s.config.MaxConcurrentRequests))\n77: \tif s.logger != nil {\n78: \t\tv1.Use(loggingMiddleware(s.logger))\n79: \t\tv1.Use(recoveryMiddleware(s.logger))\n80: \t}\n81: \n82: \tv1.GET(\"/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path\", s.handleAgentInvoke)\n83: \tv1.POST(\"/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path\", s.handleAgentInvoke)\n84: \n85: \tv1.GET(\"/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path\", s.handleCodeInterpreterInvoke)\n86: \tv1.POST(\"/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path\", s.handleCodeInterpreterInvoke)\n87: }\n88: \n89: func (s *Server) handleHealthLive(c *gin.Context) {\n90: \tc.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\"status\": \"alive\"})\n91: }\n92: \n93: func (s *Server) handleHealthReady(c *gin.Context) {\n94: \tif s.sessionManager == nil {\n95: \t\tc.JSON(http.StatusServiceUnavailable, gin.H{\n96: \t\t\t\"status\": \"not ready\",\n97: \t\t\t\"error\":  \"session manager not available\",\n98: \t\t})\n99: \t\treturn\n100: \t}\n101: \tc.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\"status\": \"ready\"})\n102: }\n103: \n104: func (s *Server) handleAgentInvoke(c *gin.Context) {\n105: \ts.handleInvoke(c, types.AgentRuntimeKind)\n106: }\n107: \n108: func (s *Server) handleCodeInterpreterInvoke(c *gin.Context) {\n109: \ts.handleInvoke(c, types.CodeInterpreterKind)\n110: }\n111: \n112: func (s *Server) handleInvoke(c *gin.Context, kind string) {\n113: \tnamespace := c.Param(\"namespace\")\n114: \tname := c.Param(\"name\")\n115: \tinvocationPath := c.Param(\"path\")\n116: \n117: \tsessionID := c.GetHeader(\"x-agentcube-session-id\")\n118: \n119: \tctx := c.Request.Context()\n120: \n121: \tsandbox, err := s.sessionManager.GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)\n122: \tif err != nil {\n123: \t\ts.handleGetSandboxError(c, err)\n124: \t\treturn\n125: \t}\n126: \n127: \tif len(sandbox.EntryPoints) == 0 {\n128: \t\tc.JSON(http.StatusNotFound, gin.H{\n129: \t\t\t\"error\": \"no entry point configured\",\n130: \t\t\t\"code\":  \"NO_ENTRY_POINT\",\n131: \t\t})\n132: \t\treturn\n133: \t}\n134: \n135: \tif err := s.storeClient.UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sandbox.SessionID, time.Now()); err != nil {\n136: \t\ts.logger.Error(\"failed to update session activity\", \"error\", err)\n137: \t}\n138: \n139: \tentryPoint := selectEntryPoint(sandbox.EntryPoints, invocationPath)\n140: \tif entryPoint == nil {\n141: \t\tc.JSON(http.StatusNotFound, gin.H{\n142: \t\t\t\"error\": \"no matching entry point\",\n143: \t\t\t\"code\":  \"NO_ENTRY_POINT\",\n144: \t\t})\n145: \t\treturn\n146: \t}\n147: \n148: \ttarget, err := buildTargetURL(entryPoint)\n149: \tif err != nil {\n150: \t\tc.JSON(http.StatusInternalServerError, gin.H{\"error\": \"invalid target endpoint\"})\n151: \t\treturn\n152: \t}\n153: \n154: \tvar jwt string\n155: \tif kind == types.SandboxKind || kind == types.SandboxClaimKind {\n156: \t\tif s.jwtManager != nil {\n157: \t\t\tjwt, err = s.jwtManager.GenerateToken(map[string]interface{}{\n158: \t\t\t\t\"session_id\": sandbox.SessionID,\n159: \t\t\t\t\"sandbox_id\": sandbox.SandboxID,\n160: \t\t\t\t\"namespace\":  sandbox.SandboxNamespace,\n161: \t\t\t\t\"name\":       sandbox.SandboxName,\n162: \t\t\t})\n163: \t\t\tif err != nil {\n164: \t\t\t\tc.JSON(http.StatusInternalServerError, gin.H{\n165: \t\t\t\t\t\"error\": \"jwt signing failed\",\n166: \t\t\t\t\t\"code\":  \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\",\n167: \t\t\t\t})\n168: \t\t\t\treturn\n169: \t\t\t}\n170: \t\t}\n171: \t}\n172: \n173: \tproxy := httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy(target)\n174: \tproxy.Transport = s.httpTransport\n175: \n176: \trpw := newReverseProxy(target, jwt, sandbox.SessionID)\n177: \tproxy.Director = rpw.Director\n178: \tproxy.ModifyResponse = rpw.ModifyResponse\n179: \tproxy.ErrorHandler = rpw.ErrorHandler\n180: \n181: \tproxy.ServeHTTP(c.Writer, c.Request)\n182: \n183: \tif err := s.storeClient.UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sandbox.SessionID, time.Now()); err != nil {\n184: \t\ts.logger.Error(\"failed to update session activity after proxy\", \"error\", err)\n185: \t}\n186: }\n187: \n188: func (s *Server) handleGetSandboxError(c *gin.Context, err error) {\n189: \tif apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n190: \t\tc.JSON(http.StatusNotFound, gin.H{\"error\": err.Error()})\n191: \t\treturn\n192: \t}\n193: \n194: \tif apiStatus, ok := err.(apierrors.APIStatus); ok {\n195: \t\tcode := int(apiStatus.Status().Code)\n196: \t\tif code == 0 {\n197: \t\t\tcode = http.StatusInternalServerError\n198: \t\t}\n199: \t\tmsg := apiStatus.Status().Message\n200: \t\tif msg == \"\" {\n201: \t\t\tmsg = err.Error()\n202: \t\t}\n203: \t\tif code == http.StatusInternalServerError {\n204: \t\t\tmsg = \"internal server error\"\n205: \t\t}\n206: \t\tc.JSON(code, gin.H{\"error\": msg})\n207: \t\treturn\n208: \t}\n209: \n210: \tif routerErr, ok := err.(APIStatus); ok {\n211: \t\tc.JSON(routerErr.Status(), gin.H{\n212: \t\t\t\"error\": routerErr.Message(),\n213: \t\t\t\"code\":  routerErr.Code(),\n214: \t\t})\n215: \t\treturn\n216: \t}\n217: \n218: \tc.JSON(http.StatusInternalServerError, gin.H{\"error\": \"internal server error\"})\n219: }\n220: \n221: func (s *Server) Start(ctx context.Context) error {\n222: \tif s.config.EnableTLS {\n223: \t\tif s.config.TLSCert == \"\" || s.config.TLSKey == \"\" {\n224: \t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"TLS cert and key are required when EnableTLS is true\")\n225: \t\t}\n226: \t\tgo s.waitForShutdown(ctx)\n227: \t\treturn s.httpServer.ListenAndServeTLS(s.config.TLSCert, s.config.TLSKey)\n228: \t}\n229: \n230: \tgo s.waitForShutdown(ctx)\n231: \treturn s.httpServer.ListenAndServe()\n232: }\n233: \n234: func (s *Server) waitForShutdown(ctx context.Context) {\n235: \t<-ctx.Done()\n236: \n237: \tshutdownCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 10*time.Second)\n238: \tdefer cancel()\n239: \n240: \ts.httpServer.Shutdown(shutdownCtx)\n241: }\n242: \n243: func (s *Server) Stop() error {\n244: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 10*time.Second)\n245: \tdefer cancel()\n246: \treturn s.httpServer.Shutdown(ctx)\n247: }\n248: \n249: func (s *Server) GetEngine() *gin.Engine {\n250: \treturn s.engine\n251: }\n\n(End of file - total 251 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package router\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"net/http/httputil\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n\tapierrors \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n)\n\ntype Server struct {\n\tconfig         *Config\n\tengine         *gin.Engine\n\thttpServer     *http.Server\n\tsessionManager SessionManager\n\tstoreClient    Store","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/server.go","time":{"start":1775852182112,"end":1775852182134}}}}
